cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper deals with stochastic computation graphs (SCGs) and their use in optimization problems arising in artificial intelligence, including supervised, unsupervised, and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as these are the most relevant sub-categories for this topic. Additionally, since the paper introduces concepts from reinforcement learning, cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories.
